TI  - Traditional fishing gears used by the fisher folk of Chatla floodplain area, Barak valley, Assam.
T2  - Indian Journal of Traditional Knowledge
M3  - Journal article
AB  - A survey was conducted for a period of 18 months (January 2010-September 2011) on 150 fish farmers of Chatla floodplain area to document the traditional fishing gears and fishing practices prevailing among them. It is found that the fishermen of Chatla floodplain area use different types of fishing gears depending upon the species and size of fish. Almost all the gears are hand made with bamboo, cane, cotton and sometimes nylon threads following primitive technologies.
