AU  - Van Dan, Truong
TI  - Assessment of impacts of climate change in fisheries and agriculture in the coastal area of Thua Thien Hue province, Vietnam.
T2  - Discussion Paper Series - Southeast Asian Regional Center for Graduate Study and Research in Agriculture (SEARCA)
M3  - Bulletin
AB  - This research addressed the following objectives: identify climate change trends and climate extreme events; and assess impacts of climate change on the fisheries (including fishing and aquaculture) and agriculture sectors. Four coastal districts in the Thua Thien Hue province, including Phong Dien, Quang Dien, Phu Vang, and Phu Loc were selected in this study. In each district, three to four communes were selected to carry out investigation and research. The outputs from the study sites were applied in the other coastal areas in the central region of Vietnam and Thua Thien Hue province in particular. To evaluate impacts of climate change on fisheries and agriculture production in the research areas, investigation through participatory rural appraisal (PRA) was conducted. Through data collection and analysis, it was found that over time, weather conditions and climate in Thua Thien Hue showed complicated movements, abnormal changes such as droughts, and prolonged heat waves often occurring during the dry season from May to August every year. Meanwhile, cold weather lasted longer during the rainy season (October to February). Floods and typhoons have occurred with stronger intensities, and tide amplitude has changed drastically. All these have had significant impacts on agriculture and fisheries activities in the province.
