TI  - Climate-smartBrachiariagrasses for improving livestock production in East Africa.
T2  - Tropical Grasslands - Forrajes Tropicales
M3  - Journal article
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - This paper describes an inter-institutional research program aimed to increase feed availability in action areas of the target countries in East Africa (e.g. Kenya, Rwanda) by use of climate-smartBrachiariaforage grasses for increased animal productivity and for generation of extra income by smallholder farmers. The program is focused on 4 major objectives: (1) determination of the role of endophytes in improving adaptation ofBrachiariagrasses to climate change (drought) and development of novel methods to detect endophytes; (2) quantification of the contribution to mitigation of climate change byBrachiariagrasses adapted to drought and low soil fertility; (3) determination of the role of improvedBrachiariagrasses integrated into mixed smallholder crop-livestock systems in improving milk and meat production in grazing and cut-and-carry forage systems, and assessment of their impact in reducing land degradation; and (4) establishment of systems for the creation of forage seed production and marketing enterprises for poor farmers, mainly females.
