AU  - Gautam, U.
AU  - Rajbhandari, B. P.
TI  - A preliminary study on the role of organic agriculture in food security at Tamankhola Rural Municipality, Baglung.
T2  - Nepalese Journal of Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The survey on "Role of Organic Agriculture on food security and livelihood at Tamankhola Rural Municipality" was conducted with the general objective to assess the food security status and livelihood of households of Tamankhola Rural Municipality through the help of organic agriculture. The method of survey was mainly focused on collecting data by directly interviewing with targeted groups such as farmers, consumers through random selection. The study was carried out from 15th June, to 17th August 2018. The total sample size was 100 consisting of every types of farmers (subsistence farmers and commercial farmers). In most places of Tamankhola rural municipality farmers do not cultivate crops during winter season because of natural abnormalities like heavy wind, frost and hailstorm. The study showed that 11% of the households had food sufficiency up to 3 months, 43% up to 6 months, 37% up to 9 months and only 9% up to 12 months from own farm production. Estimation of Household Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS) revealed that among the food insecure households 41 percent of the households were severely food insecurity. It is recommended that the local government of the rural municipality should opt for effective programme to address the situation of food insecurity.
