AU  - Jahi, A.
ED  - Bessette, G.
TI  - From resource-poor users to natural resource managers: a case from West Java.
T2  - People, land & water: participatory development communication for natural resource management
M3  - Book chapter
AB  - Along the Cimanuk River in West Java, Indonesia, efforts to prohibit agriculture on the raised riverbanks to curb seasonal flooding irremediably failed until viable economic alternatives were introduced. Through participatory development communication, the dialogue between researchers, decision-makers and small and landless farmers made it possible for sheep raising to be introduced and to flourish as an alternative to the practice of crop-based agriculture on the riverbanks that was making villages more vulnerable to annual flooding. This chapter highlights the communication tools used in this initiative, the promising results achieved, and the problems encountered.
