AU  - Zhao, Han-xiao
AU  - Cheng, Lu-ming
TI  - Research on the satisfaction of Xinjiang family farms with crop insurance and its influencing factors.
T2  - Journal of Anhui Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Objective: To study the satisfaction of family farms in Crop insurance in Xinjiang, so as to promote the high-quality development of Crop insurance in Xinjiang. Methods: Taking the family farms in Xinjiang as the survey objects, 363 family farmers were surveyed, and the basic characteristics, cognition of Crop insurance, and satisfaction with Crop insurance were analyzed. The binary logistic model was used to explore the factors that affect the satisfaction of family farms in Crop insurance. Result: Age, educational background, years of operation, degree of satisfaction with agricultural insurance products, participation in agricultural insurance related lectures, experience of agricultural natural disasters, trust in insurance companies, and satisfaction with agricultural insurance company services are 8 significant factors that affect the satisfaction of Xinjiang family farms with agricultural insurance. Conclusion: Strengthen the publicity and popularization of Crop insurance knowledge, improve and expand the product guarantee scope of Crop insurance, improve the service quality of Crop insurance enterprises, and optimize the policy based Crop insurance subsidy policy.
