TI  - Impact analysis of cyclones to agriculture and adoption of management techniques by the farmers - a case study in coastal districts of Andhra Pradesh.
T2  - Current Biotica
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The study was undertaken with the objective of assessing the nature and extent of loss to agriculture and allied fields due to the crisis of cyclone and to analyse the different mitigation techniques and management practices adopted by farmers to overcome the crisis effectively. The findings of the study revealed that the cyclones of 2005 and 2006 caused considerable damage to the crops and majority of the respondents had medium level of adoption with respect to crisis management. As majority of the respondents were small and marginal farmers, adopted measures that incur less investment to manage the crisis of cyclone. Besides physical losses, some of the respondents were subjected to shock and frustration especially the aged and women, after witnessing the damages caused due to cyclone.
