AU  - Abadi, Asfaw
AU  - Abebe, Tora
AU  - Menza, Mesfin
AU  - Syraji, Yonas
TI  - Impact of small-scale irrigation on the food security status of rural households in Ethiopia.
T2  - Journal of Agriculture and Food Research
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This review assesses the impact of small-scale irrigation (SSI) on the food security status of rural households in Ethiopia by synthesizing 48 empirical studies published between 2000 and 2023. Despite Ethiopia's significant water resources and agricultural potential, food insecurity remains widespread, exacerbated by climate variability, infrastructural gaps, and unequal access to productive assets. SSI defined as systems covering less than 200 ha emerges as a key pathway to enhance household food security through increased food availability, improved income-based access, and greater dietary diversity. The review employs a systematic literature review (SLR) guided by PRISMA protocols to ensure methodological rigor. Findings highlight geographic and gender disparities in SSI access, with lowland regions such as Afar and Somali critically underserved and women facing systemic barriers in land tenure, finance, and water governance. To equitably scale SSI, the review recommends investment in climate-resilient infrastructure, solar-powered technologies, women's land rights, and inclusive governance structures. Ultimately, SSI is positioned not just as a technical intervention, but as a strategic policy tool for building climate-resilient and inclusive rural food systems in Ethiopia.
