AU  - Castel, A.
AU  - Faysse, N.
AU  - El-Hirch, A.
AU  - Rinaudo, J. D.
TI  - Vulnerability, resilience and ability to develop family farms in the irrigated area of Bittit (Saiss plain).
T2  - Alternatives Rurales
M3  - Journal article
AB  - In the irrigated area of Bittit (in the Saiss plains, Morocco), family farms face an economic context that is more and more constraining. This study looked at how 157 family farmers in this area assess their economic vulnerability, resilience and ability to grow. Most farms are located along the same evolutionary trajectory over the last 30 years, which can be divided into four phases: initial capital accumulation, increase of production capacities, optimization of technico-economic performances and introduction of fruit growing. The main constraints and risks facing farms are the variability of market prices, the difficulty of accessing subsidies, hail and frost, and phytosanitary problems. In the short term, the main projects of the farms are to increase the cultivated areas and develop dairy farming and arboriculture. Farmers emphasize the difficulty of initiating or succeeding in such projects by acting on an individual basis. They highlight the relevance of collective action. However, support would be useful so that the farmers of Bittit concretize such collective projects.
