AU  - Rajesh Kumar, Rajesh Kumar
AU  - Hemant Kumar, Hemant Kumar
TI  - Pulses production issues in Bundelkhand Region of Uttar Pradesh.
T2  - Agricultural Situation in India
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper discusses key issues in pulses production in the Bundelkhand region of Uttar Pradesh, based on a study conducted in 2007-10 in Hamirpur district. Those issues are: (1) unavailability of quality seeds; (2) losses from insects and diseases; (3) lack of water for irrigation; (4) lack of technological awareness and knowledge; (5) weed problem during kharif season; (6) droughts and unfavourable weather conditions; (7) the tradition of Anna Pratha; (8) poor soils and their variability; (9) inadequate agricultural extension services; (10) lack of manure and fertiliser use; (11) small and marginal farmers; (12) low socioeconomic status; and (13) seasonal migration and lack of interest in youth.
