TI  - Present status of adoption of artificial insemination (AI) in dairy animals in different agroclimatic regions of Punjab.
T2  - Indian Journal of Dairy Science
M3  - Journal article
AB  - India is enjoying top position in milk production in the whole world. This is not due to the high production from the animals but due to large bovine population. The poor production of the animals could be due to many factors and one important factor is low genetic potential of the animals. Artificial Insemination (Al) is one of the most important biotechnological tool that has been developed to bring genetic improvement of animals. This study was conducted to know the present status of adoption of AI in six different agroclimatic regions of Punjab. The data were collected from 180 dairy farmers, 30 each from six agroclimatic regions with the help of structured interview schedule. Overall adoption of AI in both cows and buffaloes was 50.56 per cent in Punjab which was highest in flood plain region (66.67%) and lowest in western region (336.67%). In cows 41.67 per cent of the respondents adopted AI, which was highest in flood plain region (60.00%) and lowest in western region (30.00%). However, in buffaloes only 17.78 per cent of the respondents adopted AI, which was highest in western plain region (33.33%) and lowest in central plain region (6.67%).
