AU  - Zuo, Wen-jie
AU  - Cheng, Wen-jing
AU  - Stanny, Monika
AU  - Du, Guo-ming
TI  - Research on farmers' livelihood vulnerability to drought and its influencing factors in the agro-pastoral ecotone of northern China:a study of Yuyang District, Shaanxi Province.
T2  - Journal of Agricultural Resources and Environment
M3  - Journal article
AB  - In order to reveal the differences of farmers' livelihood vulnerability to drought in China's agro-pastoral ecotone, this study took Yuyang District of Shaanxi Province as an example, established an evaluation model of farmers ' livelihood vulnerability from the perspectives of exposure, sensitivity and adaptability. Based on the data collected through surveying 421 farmers with questionnaires in 2022, the paper evaluated farmers' livelihood vulnerability to drought and identified the influencing factors by using the obstacle model. The results showed that the livelihood vulnerability of the surveyed farmers was at a high level as a whole. Householder had never been to school, householder of primary school and pure farmers were those of highest vulnerability, with 1.767, 1.009 and 0.967 respectively. Livelihood vulnerability was negatively correlated with nonagricultural livelihood and householders ' education while it positively correlated with householders' age. The loss of crops caused by natural disasters and no guaranteed agricultural product transaction were the main factors to high livelihood exposure and sensitively separately. Householders ' education and family social relationship were the main influential factors to farmers' livelihood adaptability. The research shows that the livelihood vulnerability of different types of farmers is significantly different. On the whole, the higher level the householder 's education and younger age and the more diversified livelihood strategies indicate lower livelihood vulnerability, and vice versa. Based on the research results, this paper puts forward with policies and measures to improve the farmers' climate resilience in China's agro-pastoral ecotone.
