TI  - Drought, agricultural risk and rural income - case of a water limiting rice production environment, Tamil Nadu.
T2  - Economic and Political Weekly
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper explores agricultural risks and the ways of managing it, particularly in a water-limiting environment. The paper is based on secondary data (1970/71-2002/03) collected from various published sources for Tamil Nadu and various water-limiting rice production environments (namely, Ramnad, Thiruvallur, Sivaganga and Coimbatore districts), and farm survey data collected for the years between 2001-02 and 2003-04 from 230 farm households spreading all these districts. Sections of the paper discuss: drought; risk of input use; HYVs adoption and yield risk; price risk; and income risk.
